40:23.688 --> 40:36.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Next: one company's
attempt to bring textile jobs to
rural America through

40:36.267 --> 40:38.803 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
an unusual approach.

40:38.803 --> 40:42.440 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Hari Sreenivasan is
back with that story.

40:42.440 --> 40:48.313 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: It doesn't
look like the textile mill towns
of New England and it's

40:48.313 --> 40:51.683 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
certainly not Silicon Valley.

40:51.683 --> 40:57.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yet here in Pagosa Springs,
Colorado, a mountain town of
less than 2,000 people, an
upstart

40:57.088 --> 41:02.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
company hopes to disrupt the
textile industry using a
high-tech, outside-the-box
approach.

41:02.593 --> 41:06.431 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The company is called Voormi, a
made-up name for a mythological
mountain creature.

41:06.431 --> 41:12.070 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And it was started by former

41:12.070 --> 41:18.042 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
His idea?

41:18.042 --> 41:23.214 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To manufacture a brand-new kind
of fabric from locally sourced
materials and then sew

41:23.214 --> 41:26.984 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the garments in small
micro-factories in rural
communities.

41:26.984 --> 41:32.123 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAN ENGLISH, Founder, Voormi:
It's more like a craft approach,
kind of like the beer industry.

41:32.123 --> 41:37.929 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We like to think, if we can take
a small batch mentality and turn
things quicker, that consumers

41:37.929 --> 41:42.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
want new, fresh things
on a regular basis.

41:42.100 --> 41:46.204 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The clothing
is made for recreation in harsh
conditions, whether that's

41:46.204 --> 41:50.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mountain biking under the
blazing sun, fishing in icy cold
streams, or climbing in all
kinds

41:50.575 --> 41:54.879 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of weather.

41:54.879 --> 41:58.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
English wanted to build his
company in a region where his
products could be sewn in the
morning

41:58.015 --> 42:01.085 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and tested in the afternoon.

42:01.085 --> 42:05.923 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So he chose Pagosa Springs,
surrounded by two million acres
of national forest.

42:05.923 --> 42:11.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAN ENGLISH: We have a large
staff of so-called mountain
professionals, whether they're
ski

42:11.529 --> 42:15.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
patrollers, or river guides or
fly fishing guides, or hunting
outfitters, that love to

42:15.800 --> 42:17.502 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
test our gear.

42:17.502 --> 42:21.873 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And these guys give us
honest, straight feedback.

42:21.873 --> 42:27.612 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: English has
chosen not to outsource to large
sewing facilities in Asia,

42:27.612 --> 42:30.982 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
where much of the once-strong
U.S. textile industry ended up.

42:30.982 --> 42:34.619 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That shift left many communities
in the U.S. devastated.

42:34.619 --> 42:39.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAN ENGLISH: What we hope to do
is provide an industry in small
rural towns that allow

42:39.690 --> 42:45.563 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people to live here, play here,
and work here without having to
have multiple jobs throughout

42:45.563 --> 42:48.032 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the year.

42:48.032 --> 42:51.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: English
eventually hopes to have as many
as 10 facilities, each with

42:51.135 --> 42:54.739 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
eight to 10 sewers, scattered
throughout Colorado.

42:54.739 --> 43:01.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Currently, he has just three,
including this one at the
company headquarters.

43:01.479 --> 43:03.748 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Twenty-four year old Joan Walker
says being able to work in the
area where she grew up

43:03.748 --> 43:06.684 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
has been a dream come true.

43:06.684 --> 43:09.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She graduated from college two
years ago with a degree in
fashion design.

43:09.887 --> 43:13.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOAN WALKER, Voormi: I was
pretty convinced that I was just
going to have to settle in

43:13.558 --> 43:17.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a city for a couple of years, or
probably longer than a couple of
years, until I could

43:17.562 --> 43:21.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do something differently to get
back to where I really wanted to
be.

43:21.666 --> 43:25.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Melinda Volger
wasn't as lucky when she
graduated from college 35 years

43:25.369 --> 43:28.005 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ago.

43:28.005 --> 43:32.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She too was a fashion design
major who wanted to return to
her hometown, but because there

43:32.109 --> 43:36.080 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
were no full-time sewing jobs,
she became a secretary, and did
sewing alterations on

43:36.080 --> 43:39.150 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the side.

43:39.150 --> 43:43.454 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now she designs and sews
full-time for Voormi, and has
just a one-minute commute,
walking

43:43.454 --> 43:46.591 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
across the back alley from
her home to the shop.

43:46.591 --> 43:51.796 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MELINDA VOLGER, Voormi: I get to
give input on the design process
from the start, through

43:51.796 --> 43:56.267 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the pattern-making, through
making the initial prototypes.

43:56.267 --> 44:00.071 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they're very accepting of
any suggestions that I have, and
we work as a team back and

44:00.071 --> 44:02.640 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
forth.

44:02.640 --> 44:05.576 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Like all of
the employees at Voormi, Volger
and Walker wear many hats.

44:05.576 --> 44:07.545 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Not only do they design and sew.

44:07.545 --> 44:11.249 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They also take shifts working
at the retail store.

44:11.249 --> 44:14.919 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CEO English says that makes the
company more responsive to the
needs of customers.

44:14.919 --> 44:17.054 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DAN ENGLISH: It's a new
way of manufacturing.

44:17.054 --> 44:20.291 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's what we believe is the
future of manufacturing.

44:20.291 --> 44:23.327 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's a very -- it's a much
more nimble experience.

44:23.327 --> 44:25.630 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
And it's a wider
range of skill set.

44:25.630 --> 44:27.698 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
And that's what
we're focused on.

44:27.698 --> 44:31.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we think that's repeatable
and scalable across the United
States, and especially in

44:31.636 --> 44:35.773 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
rural communities that
need economic development.

44:35.773 --> 44:40.912 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: University of
Denver business professor Kerry
Plemmons:

44:40.912 --> 44:44.081 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KERRY PLEMMONS, University of
Denver: Somebody like Voormi who
can say, I see a trend, jump

44:44.081 --> 44:48.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
right on that trip with what we
would call agility, and an
agility to jump on a trend,

44:48.085 --> 44:51.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and then be first to market, in
that -- because the thing about
Voormi that I think important

44:51.255 --> 44:53.658 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
