46:55.112 --> 46:59.984 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And we were having a
conversation about the talk that
black parents would give to
young

46:59.984 --> 47:03.054 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
black men about how to survive
in this country, how to comport
oneself with authorities.

47:03.054 --> 47:04.255 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: How to behave.

47:04.255 --> 47:06.257 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MYCHAL DENZEL SMITH:
How to behave.

47:06.257 --> 47:10.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And what it did was, it was
flattening the experience of
what it is to be a young black

47:10.461 --> 47:14.265 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
man in America, and to say that
that's the only thing that we
have to concern ourselves

47:14.265 --> 47:17.034 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
with.

47:17.034 --> 47:23.274 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Like, it's a big deal to --
continually to exist in a
country that upholds racist
ideas

47:23.274 --> 47:28.212 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
